In this file photo taken on June 16, 2014, South African singer Johnny Clegg performs during the 20th edition of the World Sacred Music Festival in Fez, Morocco. JOHANNESBURG - Fans have taken to social media to pay tribute to legendary South African singer Johnny Clegg following news of his death. The 66-year-old died after a long battle with pancreatic cancer. READ: SA musician Johnny Clegg has died He was diagnosed with pancreatic cancer in 2015 but continued to tour and perform around the world. Several industry friends and fans have used social media to remember the singer by sharing their fondest memories and favourite hits.